I"º<p><strong>Starter</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Feed starter.</strong> Mix 10g rye flour, 60g all-purpose flour, 70g starter, 70g filtered water.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Bagel Dough</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Make dough.</strong> Measure and mix water, starter, and fat of choice in a mixing bowl until fully combined. Measure flour and salt and add to wet mixture. Work with hands until flour is incorporated in dough and slightly sticky.</li>
  <li><strong>Cover dough.</strong> Cover dough with lid or damp towel and let sit for 1 - 3 hours.</li>
  <li><strong>Divide.</strong> Shape dough into a rough circle with hands. Divide dough using bench scraper into 8 equal pie sections.</li>
  <li><strong>Shape.</strong> Using a rolling pin, roll each section into a flat circular tortilla shape.</li>
  <li><strong>Heat Pan.</strong> Heat cast-iron pan on medium heat. You can add butter or beef tallow for cooking but it isnâ€™t required. If you do, reduce heat of pan and cook a little longer to avoid smoking.</li>
  <li><strong>Cook.</strong> Once pan is hot, place tortilla on pan and cook for about 30 seconds each side until brown and bubbles form. Repeat with remaining 7 tortillas.</li>
</ol>
